ARPS — API LIST & HOW THEY WORK

1. FIREBASE FIRESTORE
   URL     : https://firestore.googleapis.com
   Used in : firebase-config.js, all pages via import
   Purpose : The main database of the app.
   How it works:
     - Stores user accounts, SOS alerts, evacuation centers,
       and admin data in real-time collections.
     - Offline persistence is enabled (enableIndexedDbPersistence),
       so reads/writes are cached in IndexedDB. If the user is
       offline, writes (like SOS alerts) are queued and
       automatically synced when internet is restored.
     - Admin pages listen in real-time using onSnapshot() so the
       dashboard updates instantly when new data arrives.

----------------------------------------------------------------

2. NOMINATIM (OpenStreetMap Reverse Geocoding)
   URL     : https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org/reverse
   Used in : user/home.html, user/js/sos.js, user/js/map-common.js
   Purpose : Converts GPS coordinates into a readable address
             (Street, Barangay, Province).
   How it works:
     - When the user's GPS location is captured, the app sends
       the latitude and longitude to Nominatim.
     - Nominatim returns a JSON object with address fields like
       road, village (barangay), city, province, and state.
     - The app picks: road -> village/suburb -> province
       and formats it as "Street, Barangay, Province".
     - Free to use. No API key required.
     - Has a 1 request/second rate limit.

----------------------------------------------------------------

3. BIGDATACLOUD (Reverse Geocoding Fallback)
   URL     : https://api.bigdatacloud.net/data/reverse-geocode-client
   Used in : user/home.html, user/js/sos.js, user/js/map-common.js
   Purpose : Backup geocoding API when Nominatim is slow or fails.
   How it works:
     - Same concept as Nominatim — sends lat/lng, gets address back.
     - Returns a localityInfo.administrative array that specifically
       contains a "Barangay" entry for Philippine locations.
     - The app searches that array for an entry whose description
       includes "barangay" to extract the correct barangay name.
     - Also returns city and principalSubdivision (province).
     - Free to use. No API key required.

----------------------------------------------------------------

4. PHILSMS API
   URL     : https://dashboard.philsms.com/api/v3/sms/send
   Used in : user/js/sos.js
   Purpose : Sends an SMS alert to the user's emergency contact
             when SOS is triggered.
   How it works:
     - When the SOS button is pressed, the app builds a message
       containing the emergency type, location label, and time.
     - It sends a POST request to PhilSMS with the contact number
       and message, authenticated via a Bearer token.
     - If the API call fails (e.g. offline), the app falls back to
       opening the device's native SMS app using the sms: URI so
       the user can send it manually.
     - Requires a PhilSMS account and API token.

----------------------------------------------------------------

5. OPEN-METEO (Weather)
   URL     : https://api.open-meteo.com
   Used in : user/home.html, user/weather.html
   Purpose : Fetches real-time weather data based on the user's
             GPS coordinates.
   How it works:
     - After getting the user's location, the app sends the
       lat/lng to Open-Meteo.
     - Returns current temperature, weather condition code,
       wind speed, and other meteorological data.
     - The app maps the weather code to a readable description
       (e.g. "Mostly Clear", "Rainy") and displays it on the
       home screen alongside the temperature.
     - Free to use. No API key required.

----------------------------------------------------------------

6. OVERPASS API (OpenStreetMap Data)
   URL     : https://overpass-api.de/api/interpreter
   Used in : user/js/map-common.js, user/js/evacuation-page.js
   Purpose : Fetches evacuation centers, barangay halls, and
             emergency facilities near the user's location.
   How it works:
     - Sends an Overpass QL query that searches for tagged
       buildings (amenity=shelter, government=barangay, etc.)
       within a radius of the user's coordinates.
     - Returns a list of map nodes/ways with their tags and
       coordinates, which are then rendered as markers on the
       Leaflet map.
     - Free to use. No API key required.

7. LEAFLET (Map Rendering)
   URL     : CDN (unpkg.com or cdn.jsdelivr.net)
   Used in : user/js/map-common.js, user/gps.html,
             user/evacuation.html, admin/map.html
   Purpose : Renders the interactive map and handles markers,
             popups, accuracy circles, and tile layers.
   How it works:
     - Leaflet is a JavaScript mapping library loaded from CDN.
     - It displays map tiles from OpenStreetMap tile servers.
     - The app creates markers for the user's location and for
       nearby evacuation centers.
     - Accuracy circles show the GPS precision radius.
     - Cached by the service worker after first load so maps
       are partially available offline.

8. OPENSTREETMAP TILE SERVER
   URL     : https://tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png
   Used in : user/js/map-common.js (via Leaflet)
   Purpose : Provides the actual map images (tiles) displayed
             in the background of the interactive map.
   How it works:
     - Leaflet requests tiles based on the current zoom level
       and map position.
     - Each tile is a 256x256 PNG image of a map section.
     - Free to use under the OpenStreetMap tile usage policy.
     - Tiles are cached by the service worker after first load.

9. TAILWIND CSS CDN
   URL     : https://cdn.tailwindcss.com
   Used in : All HTML pages
   Purpose : Provides all the utility CSS classes used for
             layout, spacing, colors, and typography.
   How it works:
     - Loaded as a script tag. It scans the HTML for class names
       and generates the necessary CSS on the fly.
     - Cached by the service worker so the UI stays styled
       even when offline.

10. GOOGLE FONTS
    URL     : https://fonts.googleapis.com
              https://fonts.gstatic.com
    Used in : shared.css
    Purpose : Loads the "Plus Jakarta Sans" and "DM Sans"
              typefaces used throughout the app.
    How it works:
      - shared.css imports the fonts via @import.
      - Google returns CSS with font-face declarations pointing
        to the actual font files on fonts.gstatic.com.
      - Both are cached by the service worker after first load
        so text renders correctly offline.

